{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.3",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 3 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:1",
      "text": "After this opened Job his mouth, and cursed his day.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:2",
      "text": "And Job spake, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:3",
      "text": "Let the day perish wherein I was born, and the night in which it was said, There is a man child conceived.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:4",
      "text": "Let that day be darkness; let not God regard it from above, neither let the light shine upon it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:5",
      "text": "Let darkness and the shadow of death stain it; let a cloud dwell upon it; let the blackness of the day terrify it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:6",
      "text": "As for that night, let darkness seize upon it; let it not be joined unto the days of the year, let it not come into the number of the months.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:7",
      "text": "Lo, let that night be solitary, let no joyful voice come therein.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:8",
      "text": "Let them curse it that curse the day, who are ready to raise up their mourning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:9",
      "text": "Let the stars of the twilight thereof be dark; let it look for light, but have none; neither let it see the dawning of the day:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:10",
      "text": "Because it shut not up the doors of my mother’s womb, nor hid sorrow from mine eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:11",
      "text": "Why died I not from the womb? why did I not give up the ghost when I came out of the belly?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:12",
      "text": "Why did the knees prevent me? or why the breasts that I should suck?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:13",
      "text": "For now should I have lain still and been quiet, I should have slept: then had I been at rest,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:14",
      "text": "With kings and counsellors of the earth, which built desolate places for themselves;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:15",
      "text": "Or with princes that had gold, who filled their houses with silver:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:16",
      "text": "Or as an hidden untimely birth I had not been; as infants which never saw light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:17",
      "text": "There the wicked cease from troubling; and there the weary be at rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:18",
      "text": "There the prisoners rest together; they hear not the voice of the oppressor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:19",
      "text": "The small and great are there; and the servant is free from his master.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:20",
      "text": "Wherefore is light given to him that is in misery, and life unto the bitter in soul;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:21",
      "text": "Which long for death, but it cometh not; and dig for it more than for hid treasures;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:22",
      "text": "Which rejoice exceedingly, and are glad, when they can find the grave?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:23",
      "text": "Why is light given to a man whose way is hid, and whom God hath hedged in?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:24",
      "text": "For my sighing cometh before I eat, and my roarings are poured out like the waters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:25",
      "text": "For the thing which I greatly feared is come upon me, and that which I was afraid of is come unto me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.3.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 3:26",
      "text": "I was not in safety, neither had I rest, neither was I quiet; yet trouble came.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
